article.headline: Eastern Michigan 63, Eastern Illinois 51
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Jarred Axon had 15 points and Jesse Bunkley scored 12 of his 13 points in the second half Thursday to rally Eastern Michigan to a 63-51 victory over Eastern Illinois. Justin Dobbins also added 12 points for the Eagles (3-8), who have won two of their last three games. Eastern Michigan played without second-leading scorer Carlos Medlock who was recovering from a hip injury he received Friday at Tulsa. Romain Martin scored 17 points and Ousmane Cisse had nine for the Panthers (5-9), who have dropped four straight games. After trailing 32-27 at halftime, Eastern Michigan took advantage of four Eastern Illinois turnovers and scored the first eight points of the second half to take its first lead since midway through the opening half. The teams traded the lead twice and were tied twice before the Eagles went on a 13-0 run and built a 50-39 advantage with 6:25 left. Bunkley keyed the spurt with nine points.
